Package Attributes

Class FunctionAttribute

  • java.lang.Object
    • AbstractObjects.ItemWithId
      • Attributes.Attribute
        • Attributes.FunctionAttribute
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class FunctionAttribute
extends Attribute
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class represents attributes which are computed by combining the attribute values of other attributes. The choices for the lambda-expression are:
    1. it is a unary function depending on one further attribute
    2. it is a binary function depending on two further attributes
    3. it is a unary function depending on an array of further attributes.
    The functions ar applied to the ConcreteDomain Values (e.g. Integer) or to the Concepts, not to the DataObjects

      • setBinaryFunction

        public void setBinaryFunction​(java.lang.String scriptText,
                              java.util.function.BiFunction<java.lang.Object,java.lang.Object,DataObject> twoFunction,
                              Attribute attribute1,
                              Attribute attribute2)
        adds a binary function for processing the attribute values of two attributes. For both attributes a stream is generated and the values of the two streams are one-by-one combined with the function. The scriptText is only necessary if the attribute is to be serialized and the function itself is not serializable.
        Parameters:
        scriptText - a textual representation for the function.
        twoFunction - the function itself
        attribute1 - the first attribute whose values are to be processed.
        attribute2 - the second attribute whose values are to be processed.

      • stream

        public java.util.stream.Stream<DataObject> stream​(Concept concept,
                                                  Scope scope,
                                                  Operators operator,
                                                  DataObject otherValue,
                                                  java.lang.Object otherConstraints,
                                                  Context context)
        generates a stream of attribute values for the concept. If only for one attribute the values are to be processed then operator, otherValue and otherConstraints can be used to filter the values of the url-attribute. If two or more attributes are to be combined then 'operator, otherValue and otherConstraints' is used in a uniform way to filter the attribute values of all attributes. This may not always make sense and therefore should be used carefully.
        Specified by:
        stream in class Attribute
        Parameters:
        concept - a concept with some attributes
        scope - the scope of the value to be returned.
        operator - for checking 'this.value operator otherValue'
        otherValue - the value to be compared with the operator.
        otherConstraints - a map of attribute - dataObject constraints
        context - the context
        Returns:
        a stream of attribute values.
